metadata.name: fx(Toadz) CC
metadata.description:
fx(Toadz) CC are Cryptoadz (cryptoadz.io) on fx(hash) which can change color. Using the power of CC0 artwork, you can now acquire a toad on the Tezos blockchain. This time it comes with a monochrome variant.

Each toad is randomly generated at mint, trait rarities are based on the tx hash from mint and do not match "real" toadz rarities. The final distribution of attributes cannot be known until all fx(Toadz) are minted.

Artwork (PNG layers) is courtesy of the Cryptoadz team and toadztoolz.com (via CC0/public domain), randomization is powered by PureSpider template and the fx(rand) on fx(hash) platform.

metadata.name: PSYCHOGEOGRAPHIC MAP
metadata.description:
The psychogeographic maps are a proposal for the construction of an artistic journey guided by the principle of walking as a poetic practice that arises through the Situationist artistic movement in the years 1952-1975 in France. The Situationist proposal was to experience a journey without a defined direction in order to make this journey a work of art, an artistic, poetic, social and personal experience.

This map will guide your luck, choose or be chosen by the lines that will guide your next journey, maybe these lines will lead you to your love, your success, your true life, or maybe they will lead you to failure, you will only know if you decide to have your own psychogeographic map of your next journey.

I know I will use all the money from the sale of this work to travel, I also don't know how far they will take me, but I will get there.



The journey is inevitable and where you can get with it is unimaginable, maybe you get there only psychogeographically, but I recommend that you also get there geographically.

Maps and Draw Layers in PNG using @purespider's open Code. 

2022- Caró, Brazil (for a while)

metadata.name: SUH-DOH-KUH - The Silver Collection
metadata.description:
After the Bronze collection, now the silver collection!

The art of solving a sudoku puzzle.
The objective is to fill a 9 × 9 grid with digits so that each column, each row, and each of the nine 3 × 3 subgrids that compose the grid contain all of the digits from 1 to 9.

The puzzle is solvable, this one is at level 'hard', good luck!

Have fun playing your very own sudoku!

Made with P5JS.

-- 385 color possibilities with the white color

Rhaegar / March 2022

metadata.name: ProcGen Entomology
metadata.description:
Realtime 3D in-browser procedural generation of insect-like models, with a look reminiscent of vintage entomology illustrations.

The project is about the fact that insects are cool first and foremost.
This is also about nostalgia.

Everything is procedural except for the font. The exposed features only describe the most visible parts.

I wrote mord words, about where it came from, and some technical details on the procedural aspect at:
https://ulucode.com/projects/entomology/

GPU Required!

Interface : 
Space : show/hide menu
Mouse Left : Rotate
Mouse Right : Pan
Mouse Middle/Wheel : Zoom

Captures only work in Live mode.

metadata.name: Ignorance is Bliss
metadata.description:
"Ignorance is Bliss" is the second collection released as a part of NeoMent's "Abandoned Reality" series.

People often argue over things that are not under their control. But why bother? At the end of the day, your opinion won't change anything unless you have the power to accomplish that change. Of course you can say that you are aguing for "The Truth" or "Justice", but what's the point in your bickering if you aren't going to accomplish anything?
But you can go even further than that, you can choose to ignore global problems completely, live in your own world. One who doesn't know of a problem shan't worry about it - thus, ignorance is bliss. 
Is it right or is it wrong? What's the point in arguing over what I wrote if you won't change anything? All you can do is decide for yourself.

metadata.name: Underwater
metadata.description:
The figures vary deterministically in number (between 10 and 20), movement, rotation and shape. The background can be black and white or colored, oriented from top to bottom or vice versa.
To produce the movement of the figures I use algorithms with sine according to their relative position on the screen. I find these movements somewhat hypnotic and try to create a sense of relaxation in the viewer. 

The project was made in P5js by Diego de los Campos in March 2022 and uses the NFT License 2.0

metadata.name: (re)generative tigers
metadata.description:
Only 2967 tigers remain in the wild. This project aims at raising funds and awareness around tiger conservation.

Every stripe is unique, much like these NFTs. To help ensure that Bengal tigers can continue to regenerate their numbers, this special generative NFT collection will aid conservation efforts to create ample corridors for every remaining tiger to roam free and repopulate.

The Corbett Foundation is a non-profit, non-governmental organization that is fully dedicated to the cause of wildlife conservation.

This first release contains 2000 editions, of a total of 2967 (re)generative tigers, that will be released, based on images from real tigers in the wild. Created by @radarboy3000

metadata.name: New World
metadata.description:
A New World can form out of destruction or creation.

Inspiration: 
The forms that appear in New World evoke cliffs, islands, and other natural structures, but perspective distortions bend them into a surreal and new computational reality. 

The collection was in part influenced by my feelings during the first two weeks of the invasion of Ukraine. It was a time marked by anxiety, uncertainty, and disillusionment. But, New World was also inspired by the hope embodied in my creative process and the genart community. Hence, the collection takes on a double meaning: a new world can form out of destruction or creation. 

Algorithm:
The collection is completely generative and written with p5.js. It began as an exploration of the dual contouring algorithm and purposefully builds on a bug I introduced when filling the contours by selecting vertices out of winding order. 

Pricing:
Dutch Auction: 16xtz -> 12xtz -> 8xtz decreasing every 10 minutes.

Charity:
5% of the primary sales will be donated to Ukrainian humanitarian aid funds through the contract set up by @ciphrd and @Veqtor.

Controls:
Key ’s’: Save an image of the output at the current resolution (available once the piece has finished generating)
Key ‘Arrow Up’ & ‘Arrow Down’: Cycle through resolution scaling factors at increments of 1080p. 1080p is the minimum resolution. There is no maximum resolution but loading performance will worsen at higher scaling
Key ‘o’: Toggle the land outlines on or off

Browser Support:
Confirmed to work on desktop browsers (Chrome Version 99.0.4844.51, Safari v15.3, Firefox v98.0) and Safari iOS v14.8

License:
NFT License

metadata.name: Atmosphere
metadata.description:
Atmosphere is a 3D interactive and generative piece creating an organic cube or sphere.  You can turn around and zoom in or let it live.
The size, position and frequency of shapes are generated for each token, along with the color theme.  Movements and positions are generated by a noise and a seed, it’s the same for each view.

 On live version the visual fit your screen.

Shortcuts on live version :
	- press ‘p’ to stop the motion and explore
	- press ‘f’ to launch the fullscreen mode
	- press ‘h’ to hide the cursor and `cmd/ctrl + s` to save a PNG.

Features :
	- Duo tone - Theme has 2 colors
	- Direction - Direction of the movements of shapes (x, y, none or all)
	- Rotation - Rotation of shapes (x,z, all or none)
	- Main Shape - sphere or box
	- Shapes - cylinder, cube, plane or torus 
	- Scalable - If the  motion impact the scale of shapes or not

Created by Quentin Hocdé, in Brussels (Belgium).

metadata.name: Pi Dice
metadata.description:
Happy Pi Day!!
I chose a ten-sided virtual dice to visually represent the digits of Pi.
First, I start at a random digit from 100000 digits of Pi. Then I draw the face of the die corresponding to that digit and move to next digit.
So, what you see is a slice of digits of Pi, represented by dice (or different faces of a single die).

Open the console to see the percent of occurrence of each digit in the generative token.
